===Etymology===
Old English [[Lindcoln]], from Latin [[Lindum Colonia]], from Brythonic [[Lindo]], [[Lindon]], probably from ''*linn'' ‘pool’, in reference to the [[w:Brayford Pool|Brayford]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'lɪŋkən/}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-noun|Lincoln|Lincolns}}

# A placename, originally in Lincolnshire, England.
# An English [[surname]].
# [[w:Abraham Lincoln|Abraham Lincoln]], [[President]] of the [[United States]] during the [[Civil War]].
# A brand of American [[automobile]].
# An English breed of [[sheep]].

